title: New Mexico High School Soccer Rankings
text:
New Mexico High School Soccer Rankings Kaitlyn Glass NMPreps.com Staff Writer 
Each Monday on NMPreps.com we rank the Top 25 Soccer Teams, both boys and girls are updated as of October 12th, 2015. We also recap the Team and Players of the Week. Sign Up For A Premium Subscription Now - Just 33 cents a day! Team of the Week: Roswell Boys soccer came into this week with a solid 10-2 record. They had a matchup with the Goddard Rockets where they were the clear favorite. However, the Rockets had a different plan. With 3 goals by Jonathan Sanchez that were assisted by Jorge Villa, the Rockets would go on to tie the Coyotes 3-3. Goddard had lost 1-6 previously this year. NMPreps.com Top 25 Boys Soccer Rankings NMPreps.com Top 25 Girls Soccer Rankings #1 Albuquerque Academy (13-1-1) Mercy Ruled Grants, Beat Pius #2 Albuquerque (10-4-1) Beat West Mesa Drew with Atrisco #3 Rio Rancho (13-3-1) Drew with Cleveland, Beat Santa Fe #4 La Cueva (11-2-1) Lost to La Cueva and Eldorado #8 Cibola (10-5) Blanked Santa Fe and Volcano Vista #9 Volcano Vista (7-7-1) #1 La Cueva (12- 1-1) Beat Sandia #2 St. Pius X (14-2) Mercy Ruled Moriarty, Beat Academy #3 Eldorado (12-2-1) Mercy Ruled Highland, Beat Sandia #4 Rio Rancho (9-5-2) Beat Cleveland , Mercy Ruled Santa Fe #5 Cibola (12-3) Mercy Ruled Santa Fe and Beat Volcano #6 Farmington (14-2) Blanked Miyamura and Piedra Vista #7 Hope Christian (12-3) Mercy Ruled Bloomfield and Rehoboth and Beat Prep #8 Albuquerque (12-2-1) Beat West Mesa and Atrisco #9 Cleveland (8-6-1) Boys Player of the week Girls Player of the Week Jonathan Sanchez - Goddard Leilani Baker - Rio Rancho Getting the ball in the back of the net is not a new concept to Jonathan Sanchez. Sanchez has racked in 23 goals in 12 games so far this season. He scored 3 against Ruidoso, Hatch Valley and Roswell, 4 against Portales and an impressive 6 against Robertson. However, the most important goals Sanchez has scored came this week when he knocked in 3 to tie a very powerful Roswell squad. Scoring goals against your rival high school is always an exciting thing to do. This week, Leilani Baker knocked in 2 to give the Rams a victory over rival Cleveland Storm. Baker has scored multiple goals in two other games this year, against Cibola and Onate. Baker has scored 9 goals on the season, 4 coming in district play, making her a top player in her district.
